# **3. Environment Variables**

Create `.env.local`:

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-backend-url/api/v1
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
```

Restart dev server after changes:

```
pnpm dev
```

---

# **4. API Client Layer (Next.js 16)**

`src/lib/api.ts`

```ts
export async function api(path: string, options: RequestInit = {}) {
  const res = await fetch(`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL}${path}`, {
    credentials: "include",
    ...options,
  });

  if (!res.ok) {
    const text = await res.text();
    throw new Error(text);
  }

  return res.json();
}

export const apiGet = (path: string) => api(path);

export const apiPost = (path: string, body: any) =>
  api(path, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
  });
```

---

# **5. Authentication Flow (Next.js App Router)**

### **Login**
- User submits email/password
- Backend sets HttpOnly cookie
- Frontend stores user info in React state or SWR

### **Protected Routes**
Use **Server Components** for protection:

```ts
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";
import { apiGet } from "@/lib/api";

export default async function AdminPage() {
  const user = await apiGet("/auth/me");

  if (user.role !== "ADMIN") redirect("/unauthorized");

  return <div>Admin Dashboard</div>;
}
```

